      <h1>Carrot Cake Recipe</h1>
      
        <p>In this recipe we'll learn how to make a delicious Carrot Cake

        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>6 cups grated carrots</li>
          <li>1 cup brown sugar</li>
          <li>1 cup raisins</li>
          <li>4 large eggs</li>
          <li>1 and a half cups white sugar</li>
          <li>1 cup vegetable oil</li>
          <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
          <li>1 cup crushed pineapple, drained</li>
          <li>3 cups all-purpose flour</li>
          <li>4 teaspoons ground cinnamon</li>
          <li>1 and a half teaspoons baking soda</li>
          <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
          <li>1 cup chopped walnuts</li> 
        </ul>
      
      
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Gather all ingredients.</li>
          <li>Combine grated carrots and brown sugar in a medium bowl. Let sit for 1 hour, then stir in raisins.
          <li>Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 C). Grease and flour two 10-inch round cake pans. Beat eggs in a large bowl until lighter in color.
          <li>Gradually beat in white sugar, oil, and vanilla. Stir in pineapple.
          <li>Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt in a separate bowl, then stir into egg mixture until absorbed.
          <li>Stir in carrot mixture and walnuts. Pour evenly into the prepared cake pans.
          <li>Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
          <li>Cool for 1 minutes before removing cake from the pans; let cool completely      
        </ol>
